defaultWritten evidence defaultsubmitted by defaultMilton Keynes Council default(GHS0018)defaultThis submission has been made by Geoff 
defaultSnelson
default, Director of Strategy, Milton Keynes Council and sponsor of the Milton Keynes Future City Programme.
defaultThe Future City Programme is an umbrella for a range of innovative programmes and projects including the Low Carbon Urban Transport Zone (LUTZ) programme that has an autonomous vehicles theme. 
defaultImplementation of these initiatives has benefited significantly from the involvement of the new Catapult centres.     
defaultIndividual Catapults have provided expert advice and additional capacity to develop projects. They have been able to assist in securing input from expert academic and industry partners and sharing intelligence on new and innovative developments in their respective fields. They have also acted as points of co-ordination for business and government input more widely. 
defaultOne of the most positive aspects of the Catapults is their interest in learning about practice and innovation in localities. Both bottom-up and top-down perspectives are essential to horizon scanning activity and the most effective arena for understanding the future is arguably at the level of the city, where technology and other developments can be scoped and understood within a locality context – including implementation opportunities and challenges.
